<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>A drop shadow effect renders the source with a drop shadow. The color of the drop shadow can be modified using the <db:link xlink:href="qgraphicsdropshadoweffect.xml#color-prop">setColor</db:link>() function. The drop shadow offset can be modified using the <db:link xlink:href="qgraphicsdropshadoweffect.xml#offset-prop">setOffset</db:link>() function and the blur radius of the drop shadow can be changed with the <db:link xlink:href="qgraphicsdropshadoweffect.xml#blurRadius-prop">setBlurRadius</db:link>() function.</db:para>
<db:para>By default, the drop shadow is a semi-transparent dark gray (<db:link xlink:href="qcolor.xml">QColor</db:link>(63, 63, 63, 180)) shadow, blurred with a radius of 1 at an offset of 8 pixels towards the lower right. The drop shadow offset is specified in device coordinates.</db:para>
